         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15 Oct [1859] ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ In reply to your suggestion contained in a letter of the 7 instant ¶  I have the honor to inform you that the votes you refer to No 86/84, 83/84 for fencing Zoological Garden...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">59.10.15b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Thomas Balmain</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 59/3418, unit 4, p. 183, VPRS 975/P2 outward registered correspondence, VA 669 Department of Public Works, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15 Oct [1859]</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your suggestion contained in a letter of the 7 instant<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to G. Horne, 7 October 1859.</p>
               </note> I have the honor to inform you that the votes you refer to No 86/84, 83/84 for fencing Zoological Gardens and Botanic Gardens being separate divisions of the "Appropriation Act" cannot legally be applied to the same work<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See also another letter from Balmain to M, 15 October 1859 (in this edition as 59-10-15c).</p>
               </note> I have therefore to request that you will state what course you consider should under the circumstances be adopted.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Sd for S.G.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Surveyor General.</p>
               </note>T C Balmain</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Botanic Gardens</p>
